{"questionId":"19626","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Emlyn plays many games of basketball for his school team. The number of minutes he plays in each game follows a normal distribution with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> minutes.</p>\n<p>In any game there is a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> chance he will play less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>minutes</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In any game there is a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>70</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> chance he will play less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>minutes</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The standard deviation of the number of minutes Emlyn plays in any game is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that Emlyn plays more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>minutes</mtext></math> in a game.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><img src=\"__IMG__/a109c16f0d79201a9db7072356e5a5aa30b61d28.png\"> </strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for correct probability equation <strong>OR</strong> correctly shaded diagram indicating <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><br><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>141</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>141187</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19626","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.T_6c.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that Emlyn plays more than 20 minutes in a game.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}